The paper discusses the challenges of minimizing non-convex error functions over continuous, high dimensional spaces, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization. The paper specifically focuses on the issue of saddle points, which are known to be a major obstacle in high dimensional optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory), which are also related to optimization and machine learning. The paper also discusses the application of the proposed algorithm to deep neural network training, which further supports the relevance of these categories. Additionally, the paper mentions results from statistical physics and random matrix theory, which suggest a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
